args:
Despite her disappointment, Siren is all smiles,
and her positive outlook gives courage to Cleo.
When the day of the show arrives, audience
members are few and far between. But Siren's
singing inspires them to start trickling inâ€”
along with more than a few fiends!
Hey, Luca. How did the\nconcert promotion go?
Not great. I hit a whole bunch of towns,\nand the rumors got crazier in each one.
Folks are really terrified,\nespecially in towns on the coast.
Sounds like we have a pretty\ntough road ahead of us.
You were out promoting the show and\nstuff, yeah? Soooo? How'd it go?
Yeah, I knew this wouldn't be easy.\nBut thanks for trying anyway!
Anyway, I'm gonna get back to the stage.\nGotta keep working and whatever!
She doesn't SEEM bothered,\nbut I ain't sure I'm buyin' it.
I think she's actually pretty\nbroken up about it.
If people would just give her a listen,\nthey'd know they've got her wrong!
Well, all we can do is keep working at it\nuntil the day of the performance.
Right? We still got a stage to finish,\nseats to put out, and a damn crowd to find!
If we all do our best and keep trying to\nspread the word, things will work out.
I like that attitude! Let's get out there\nand give everybody a show to remember!
Oh, wow! Did I wake you up?
I thought I was being quiet,\nbut I guess not. Hee hee!
Enough with the false bravado, Siren.\nI can see how much pain you're in.
So, what? I should cry or whatever?\nLike THAT'LL do anything!
It will make you feel better.
Why are you so determined to do this\nconcert when it's causing you such pain?
There's almost no chance it will go well,\nwhich means you will be hurt anew.
Look, before I met all you guys, I was just\nsinging to myself on empty beaches or\ndown at the bottom of the sea, you know?

No one cared about my music. Heck,
no one even HEARD it. It was all just
for me, and I was kinda okay with that.
Or, you knowâ€”I thought I was.
But then you guys all found me\nand said you WANTED me to sing!
Yeah! And that made me realize that\nsinging for myself wasn't actually what\nI wanted.
I thought I was fine, but I was actually\nSUPER lonely this whole time!
I was soooo crazy happy to be able\nto sing for all of you. It was, like,\nmy first audience in forever.
And having that audience made me\nwanna go get a BIGGER one!
I can't give up on that now.\nI'll never forgive myself.
Plus, even if not one single person\ncomes to my show...
I'll still have all of you.\nThat's way better than what I had before!
I envy you. Truly I do.
How I wish I had the strength to clearly\nsay ï¼‚I desire this thingï¼‚ and then act\nupon it in the way that you do.
Okay, stop. You DO have that strength.\nYou can do, like, ANYTHING.
If only it were so simple.
Okay, so maybe it's not easy by yourself,\nbut you've got oodles of friends!
There's nothing wrong with a helping\nhandâ€”or, like, a shove, maybe?
All you need is a little courage.
Okay, time to stop with the gloomy talk\nbefore we all turn into big downers.
I'm ready to sing something awesome!\nYou wanna stick around and hear it?
Then get the wax outta your ears, girl,\n'cause I'm gonna belt this loud and proud!
That night, lovely music echoed through the air...
Well, I guess this is all we can do.
Yeah, we only got a couple minutes\nbefore the curtain lifts.
And there ain't a single butt in the seats!
Guess this was all pretty silly.
I actually thought people would come.
Yessss! Looks like we got an audience.\n...Hey guys, welcome to Siren's concert!
I heard her singing a few days back\nand couldn't get it out of my head!
My child heard her singing last night\nand begged me to come see her.
Then get the wax outta your ears, girl,\n'cause I'm gonna belt this loud and proud!
Ohmigosh. They heard me singing!\nMy music actually reached them!
Then keep it up! Maybe you can bring\neven more folks over this way!
Yeah, let's get this show started!
Whoa! The whole earth is quakin'!\nI think we got an entire mob'a people\nwhat decided to come see the show!
Well, hellspit! Guess it ain't just folks\nwhat are bein' charmed by her tunes.
Her singin' attracts FIENDS?\nThat's really impressive!
This is no time to be appraising\nher musical talents, Luca!
Oh noooo! Now they're gonna be scared\nof me for, like, a DIFFERENT reason!
Don't worry, Siren! We'll take care of them!
Welcome to the debut performance\non the stage where dreams happen!
And now for the openin' act...\nA fiend-slayin' exhibition!
Let's keep those spirits high, folks!
